On September 11, 2010, President Obama, First Lady Michelle Obama, Vice President Biden, and Dr. Biden will commemorate the ninth anniversary of the September 11th terrorist attacks. President Obama will observe a moment of silence at the White House and then deliver remarks and participate in a wreath-laying ceremony at the Pentagon Memorial. The First Lady will be the keynote speaker at a memorial ceremony in Shanksville, Pennsylvania for the passengers and crew of United Flight 93. She will also participate in a service project at the Vinson Hall Retirement Community in Virginia. Vice President Biden and Dr. Biden will attend the September 11th Commemoration Ceremony in New York City and participate in a service activity in the area. The National Day of Service and Remembrance was established into law by the Edward M. Kennedy Serve America Act, which aims to strengthen service opportunities for Americans.